{
  "stem": "27285.2",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Again, the crowdedness of it, just quite cold, and after a few days we had to start to work.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was in a factory of ammunition, and it was-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A little small-- I don't know how to-- how you call this.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This is things that I never and I hope never again [LAUGHS] [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anyway, it was an ammunition factory, and we worked there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it-- and we went-- and it was a town which was very heavily bombarded maybe because of the factories.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Also because it was in the middle of Dresden and Kremnitz, and Dresden was completely destroyed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we were always locked into this place, and the Germans left for-- for their shelters.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we opened the window and looked around and were happy-- happy the Americans or English or whoever was coming, never thinking that they might also hit us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But you know, this is another kind of self-perseverance, that you don't think that something-- anything can happen to you at that moment.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, well, it didn't, but-- do we have time?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So when the front came closer and closer, they started to [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They couldn't kill us anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They had no time, and they had no possibilities to kill us in Oederan, so they wanted to take us to some other concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know which one.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Anyway, they didn't-- we didn't reach it anyway, because they put us into these cattle cars again, and now we started to crisscross the place without anything really.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, we got maybe some ration for the way, and that's it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was-- well, must have been-- when did the war end?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In May?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So it must have been something like April.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Still very cold and wet.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
